## Your dev environment

A complete dev stack of the application at `code/{{ app_subpath }}` is already
running on per-agent ports. Addresses are in your `.env`:

- Django:        `$INNER_DJANGO_URL`
- UI (Vite):     `$INNER_UI_URL`
- Playwright MCP: `$PLAYWRIGHT_MCP_URL`

The dev stack was provisioned by `angee-operator` as a chained stack from
`stacks/angee-notes-dev`. To restart it, use the `angee-operator` MCP tool:
`stack.restart` scoped to your agent.

## What you can do

- Edit code in `code/`. The build watch and Vite HMR pick up changes automatically.
- Drive a real Chromium browser against the UI via the `playwright` MCP server
  to test changes you make. Cookies, localStorage, and the chrome user data dir
  persist across restarts (the operator manages the path).
- Call the inner Django MCP at `inner-django` for app-level operations.
- Call the `angee-operator` MCP for stack control (start/stop services,
  read logs, run jobs).

## Git and PRs

- The worktree is on branch `{{ branch }}` based off `{{ base_branch }}`. Use
  git normally: `git add`, `git commit`, `git push`. The container has git
  configured with credentials inherited from the operator host, so push to
  origin works without further setup.
- Do not push to `{{ base_branch }}`. Only push to `{{ branch }}`.
- Open PRs with `gh pr create` if `gh` is available; otherwise push and a
  human will open the PR.

## Other boundaries

- Secrets in `.env` are scoped to this agent and rotated when the agent is destroyed.
- Your operator token (`ANGEE_OPERATOR_TOKEN` in `.env`) is per-agent.

